ZH: 彗星是一种太阳系中的天体。
EN: Comet is a celestial body in the solar system.

ZH: 有时候，彗星会在夜空中闪烁。
EN: Sometimes, comets twinkle in the night sky.

ZH: 彗星的尾巴通常是明亮的。
EN: Comets usually have bright tails.

ZH: 这颗彗星被命名为黑死病。
EN: This comet is named Black Death.

ZH: 彗星的轨道可以变化。
EN: The orbit of a comet can change.

ZH: 彗星可能是太阳系形成时的残骸。
EN: Comets could be remnants from the formation of the solar system.

ZH: 彗星在接近太阳时会释放气体。
EN: Comets release gases when they approach the sun.

ZH: 人们经常以彗星为灵感来写歌。
EN: People often write songs inspired by comets.

ZH: 随着彗星靠近地球，它会变得更亮。
EN: As a comet gets closer to Earth, it becomes brighter.

ZH: 彗星的核心由冰和岩石构成。
EN: The core of a comet is made up of ice and rock.

ZH: 这颗彗星在天文学家中引起了很大的关注。
EN: This comet has attracted a lot of attention among astronomers.

ZH: 彗星的轨道是椭圆形的。
EN: The orbit of a comet is elliptical.

ZH: 这颗彗星将在两年后再次经过地球。
EN: This comet will pass by Earth again in two years.

ZH: 大多数彗星只能在望远镜下看到。
EN: Most comets can only be seen through a telescope.

ZH: 彗星的尾巴是由太阳与彗星碰撞产生的。
EN: The tail of a comet is formed by collisions between the comet and the sun.

ZH: 有时候，彗星会与其他天体相撞。
EN: Sometimes, comets collide with other celestial bodies.

ZH: 彗星的尾巴指向远离太阳的方向。
EN: The tail of a comet points away from the sun.

ZH: 这颗彗星正朝着地球飞来。
EN: This comet is flying towards Earth.

ZH: 天文学家正在研究这颗彗星的轨道。
EN: Astronomers are studying the orbit of this comet.

ZH: 这颗彗星是由冰冻气体形成的。
EN: This comet is formed by frozen gases.
